text: Akane Yamao (, born September 30, 1974, Kiyose, Tokyo) is a Japanese rhythmic gymnast. Yamao competed for Japan in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all- around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she was 19th in the qualification round and advanced to the semifinal, where she placed 18th and did not advance to the final of 10 competitors. == References == == External links == * * Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Japanese rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Japan Category:People from Kiyose, Tokyo Category:Sportspeople from Tokyo Metropolis
